rules.sql:
performedDate IS NOT NULL 
AND performedDate != '' 
AND ( 
  TRY_CAST(performedDate AS DATE) < '1900-01-01' 
  OR TRY_CAST(performedDate AS DATE) > CURRENT_DATE 
)
rules.name: PROC005–PerformeddatereasonablenessFORperformedDate
rules.description: PROC-005 – Performed date reasonableness FOR performedDate

rules.sql: performedStartDate IS NOT NULL AND performedStartDate != ''
rules.name: PROC006–StartmustbebeforeendFORperformedStartDate
rules.description: PROC-006 – Start must be before end FOR performedStartDate

rules.sql:
ordinalityCode IS NOT NULL 
AND ordinalityCode != '' 
AND ordinalityCode NOT IN ('63161005', '2603003')
rules.name: PROC009–ValidordinalitycodeFORordinalityCode
rules.description: PROC-009 – Valid ordinality code FOR ordinalityCode

rules.sql:
performerNpi IS NOT NULL 
AND performerNpi != '' 
AND performerNpi NOT RLIKE '^\\d{10}$'
